#originalTopic=should-the-us-have-universal-healthcare
Not everyone treated at the emergency room has an actual emergency.  That's part of the problem.It does not follow that just because something benefits society that it must be coercively mandated by the government.  If that argument holds water for you then I'd suggest reading up the utilitarian arguments for capitalism and the free market.